'''The Polytechnic, Ile-Ife''', formerly '''Universal Turorial College''', is a private-owned tertiary institution located in the ancient city of [[Ile Ife]], [[Osun State]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.naij.com/520022-ooni-death-adedoyin-claims-ooni-nominated-succesor-demis.html | title=Adedoyin Claims Late Ooni Of Ife Nominated Him As Successor | work=[[Naij]] | date=15 August 2015 | accessdate=13 September 2015}}</ref> Founded in 1984 by [[Rahmon Adedoyin]], the polytechnic is recognized by the [[National Board for Technical Education]] after it was accredited in 2009.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/ooni-stool-osun-govt-to-commence-succession-process-this-week/219079/ | title=Ooni Stool: Osun Govt to Commence Succession Process This Week | work=[[Thisday]] | date=1 September 2015 | accessdate=13 September 2015 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151015123216/http://www.thisdaylive.com/articles/ooni-stool-osun-govt-to-commence-succession-process-this-week/219079/ | archivedate=15 October 2015 | df= }}</ref> The Polytechnic, Ile-Ife offers [[National Diploma (United Kingdom)|National Diploma]] and [[Higher National Diploma]] courses at [[undergraduate]] levels.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.thepolytechnicife.com/history.php | title=Polythecnic History | accessdate=13 September 2015}}</ref>
